&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;ASI is the largest global provider of technology B2B services for the $27.7 billion promotional products industry (branding and marketing). With 25,000 clients in 53 countries, our mission is to inspire, inform, and empower our clients’ success every step of the way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;ASI currently has a hybrid work model. This position requires in office presence on Tuesdays and Wednesdays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will enhance ASI&#39;s business growth by identifying and executing upgrade opportunities within our existing client base. This will be achieved through the strategic promotion and sales of ASI&#39;s products and services to both prospective and current members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Account Executive will report to the Director, Distributor Sales. You will be integrated into our distributor sales department, collaborating with a team of highly motivated sales professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your responsibilities will include targeting specific prospect and existing customer segments to meet and exceed sales objectives. We seek a candidate who is driven, client-focused, and possesses exceptional communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expected total compensation of $95,000 - $105,000 with a base of $60,000 - $70,000. Individual pay within the range will be based on role‑related experience, education, skills, and qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pro-actively identify opportunities to upgrade clients to higher-tier plans, additional services, or expanded product offerings based on their evolving needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct discovery calls and product demonstrations tailored to client goals, showcasing the value of upgraded solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintains sales activity goals, using strategies including cold calling and emailing, social media outreach, content marketing, lead generation tools, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responding timely to customer requests for information and utilizes sales skills to increase customer’s base value. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handling ASI customer inquiries and questions to appropriate resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Following prescribed sales presentations and demonstrations with accuracy and quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;College degree preferred or equivalent work experience. Highschool/ GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years of business-to-business sales experience required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in using various sales and marketing technologies, such as CRM software (e.g., Microsoft Dynamics), Microsoft programs (Outlook, Teams, Excel) and sales automation platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communications, relationship-building, and negotiation skills, as well as a proven track record of success in sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong skills in digital communication, including email outreach, virtual meetings, and webinars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to quickly adapt to new technologies and tools as they become available.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;ASI offers full-time employees a comprehensive benefits package including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical, Dental, and Vision coverage, available on day one of employment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid maternity and paternity/bonding leave (12 weeks paid for birthing/primary parent and 4 weeks paid for secondary parent) and a parent support group.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12 weeks of paid daycare for new parents (14 weeks at our onsite daycare center, Lots of Love).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Health and Wellness programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free 24/7 access to Magellan Employee Assistance Program and Teladoc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Day one 401(k) with company match.&lt;/li

